post_text:
El gobernador Greg Abbott ha declarado un desastre de salud pública y ha ordenado que todas las escuelas cierren hasta el 3 de abril de 2020 en un esfuerzo por evitar una mayor propagación de COVID-19. La Academia Jean Massieu se une a otros distritos en todo el estado para cumplir con la declaración y extender nuestro cierre actual hasta el 3 de abril, momento en el cual los funcionarios del estado y del departamento de salud volverán a evaluar la situación.
Aunque nuestro campus está cerrado, la instrucción de los estudiantes continuará. El maestro de su estudiante se comunicará con usted, si aún no le ha informado sobre cómo procederemos con la instrucción para su hijo.
Como siempre, si necesita asistencia inmediata, no dude en enviarnos un correo electrónico a mfox@jmaisd.org, or asummerlin@jmaisd.org .

post_text:
Gov. Greg Abbott has declared a Public Health Disaster and has directed all schools to close through April 3, 2020 in an effort to prevent further spread of COVID-19. Jean Massieu Academy joins other districts across the state in complying with the declaration and extending our current closure through April 3, at which time state and health department officials will reassess the situation.
Although our campus is closed, student instruction will continue. Your student’s teacher will be reaching out to you, if they haven’t already to inform you on how we will proceed with instruction for your child.
As always, if you need immediate assistance please feel free to email mfox@jmaisd.org, or asummerlin@jmaisd.org .

JMA staff, students and parents hosted and participated in the first EVER Fall Festival on Friday, Oct. 28th from 3-7 p.m. The festival was a HUGE success and fun was had by all, which was evident by all the positive comments and smiles as everyone left the campus!! Thank you to all who volunteered to ensure the festival was a success and memorable for the students at JMA. It could not have been successful without parent/guardian assistance, CONCILIO and support from our parent liaison, Ms. Gonzalez. Several staff members helped organized the festival and put in extra time in planning the event. The money raised will be added to our JMA library fund for grades pre-12. Thanks again to everyone!
Monica

Jean Massieu Academy added 3 new photos.
September 26, 2016 at 9:52 AM ·

This weekend Jean Massieu Academy made their presence at the Deaf Celebration in Dallas on Saturday, September 24, 2016 at the Tarrant County College-Trinity River Campus. JMA was represented by our Principal and Superintendent Monica Fox and our ASL teacher Randal King along with other staff members that participated. The Deaf Celebration is an exciting event that brings the Deaf and hearing communities together.

Este fin de semana Jean Massieu Academy hizo su presencia en la Celebración de Sordos en Dallas el sábado 24 de septiembre de, 2016 a Campus de Tarrant County College-Río Trinity. JMA fue representado por su Director y Superintendente Monica Fox y nuestro maestro de ASL (señas) Randal King, junto con otros miembros del personal que participaron. La Celebración de Sordos es un evento emocionante que unifica la comunidad sorda y auditivos.

All JMA parents are welcome to join in the discussion every Thursday at 9:00 am.

Great news for you and your students!
All enrolled students of Jean Massieu Academy JMAISD
are eligible to receive a healthy breakfast and lunch at school at NO CHARGE to your household each day of the 2015-2016 school year.
No further action is required of you. Your child(ren) will be able to participate in these meal programs without having to pay a fee or submit an application.
If you have child(ren) that are attending schools that are not participating in CEP, your household may still need to fill out a confidential meal application. Please call your Food Service Office if you have questions.
If we can be of any further assistance, please contact Miraida Reyes at 817-460-0396.

post_text:
Good Afternoon JMA Community!

Believe it or not, WE NEED PENCILS! We have no idea where they are all going but the students are always asking if we have more. Please search around at home and send back pencilsJ!! We’ll need them to complete the 19 more days of school that we have left. There is so much more learning to do and we’re going to be working as much as we can until the very last day! Thank you for your support.

**************************
Buenas Tardes Comunidad de JMA!

Lo creas o no, NECESITAMOS LÁPICES! No tenemos idea a donde todos se han ido pero los estudiantes siempre están preguntando si tenemos más. Por favor, buscar alrededor en su casa y enviar lápices a la escuelaJ!! Tendremos que completar los 19 días que quedan de escuela. Hay mucho más aprendizaje que hacer y vamos a estar trabajando todo lo que se pueda hasta el último día! Gracias por su ayuda.

Attention all parents and guardians of 6-12th Grade JMA Eagles!

North Lake College will be at JMA this Friday, May 8, 2015, from 9:30-11:30 a.m. to speak with our 6th through 12th graders about college admissions and applications. The presentation is entitled, “What Comes After High School?”. ALL PARENTS AND GUARDIANS ARE WELCOME TO ATTEND AND PARTICIPATE IN THIS WORKSHOP! Please get here before 9:30 as we will be starting promptly at 9:30 a.m.

Thank you

***************************

Atención a todos los padres y guardián del grado 6-12!

El colegio de North Lake estará en JMA el Viernes, 8 de mayo, 2015 esto será a las 9:30-11:30 a.m. para hablar con nuestros estudiantes del grado de 6 a 12 grado sobre admisiones y aplicaciones para colegio. La presentación será titulada “Lo que Viene después de la Escuela Secundaria?” . TODOS LOS PADRES Y GUARDIANS SERAN BIENVENIDOS A PARTICIPAR EN ESTE TALLER! Por favor llegue antes de las 9:30 ya que estaremos empezando exactamente a las 9:30 a.m.

Gracias

post_text:
Hello JMA families, friends and community members:

The administration of JMA would like to share that we have not had any contact with nor are in any way connected to the unfortunate Dallas residents who have been impacted by the Ebola virus. We continue to enforce school policies with regard to all illnesses and are ever vigilant in maintaining the safety of all students. We will be sending home a reminder that students or individuals with a fever or who are otherwise not well enough to be in school should remain at home until they have been fever free for, at least, 24 hours. Students who arrive at school with a fever or other indicators of illness will be sent home to recover. This policy holds true for JMA staff as well. Parents will be the first contacted in the extremely unlikely event that the situation changes. In any event, we encourage JMA families to contact the school with any questions or concerns about this or any other matter.

Thank you for your continued support-
Margaret R. O'Brien

post_text: Imagine how exciting it is to get both high school & college credit at the same time! On April 24 @ 6pm we will be hosting an information night at the cafeteria. Students in 6-12th grade and their parents are invited to join us. If you know a non-JMA student who can benefit from this program, they are welcomed to attend. The meeting is available in both English and Spanish.

post_text:
Dear Families,

Please join us for our first ever JMA Hot Cocoa Cafe. Bring a book, a friend or family member and come read with us on Thursday, December 5, 2013 from 5-6pm. The book fair will be open and you are welcome to shop or enjoy reading with your family and friends in the cafeteria. We want to show our students that reading is a family event. If you need a book to read, there will be some books provided to share.

We are asking parents to donate:
PK-4 grade = 1 package of hot cocoa
5th-12th = 1 package of styrofoam cups
Please send hot cocoa and cups by Thursday 12/5/13.

Thank you for supporting our students and their love of reading.

post_text: Jean Massieu Academy wants to thank KP Monaco & Assoc. for becoming involved by donating their used ink cartridges & toners for our school recycling program. An unknown fact is that it approximately takes 1 gallon of oil to create one ink cartridge. Thanks to KP Monaco their contribution will result in keeping our planet clean and allowing JMA to generate revenue for our fundraiser to purchase student computers. Plus, we also want to thank John for taking the time to drive to our school and donating the items. If a parent or student would like to thank KP Monaco & Assoc. their website is http://kpmonaco.com and Facebook page is https://www.facebook.com/kpmonaco

post_text: Jean Massieu Academy would like to thank Design Works Studio for participating in our recycling program. Sarah was kind enough to donate their used ink cartridges and toners to us. One of the benefits of recycling the used ink cartridges is that JMA will generate revenue towards our fundraiser to purchase much needed technology equipment. If you have a chance, please thank the kind folks at Design Works Studio for their contribution. Their website is http://www.designworks.net and Facebook page is https://www.facebook.com/pages/Design-Works-Studio-Inc/111680242216657
